casebody.data:
Herbert R. WILKIN, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7424. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. May 10, 1937. Edward N. Barnard, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. John C. Lehr, of Detroit, Mich., for the United States.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel, it is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed at the costs of appellant.
